      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You can observe the health of your starter by looking at its visible characteristics, which are indicators of the microbial activity. A healthy, active starter will typically exhibit a consistent, vigorous rise and fall, often with many bubbles, indicating balanced yeast and bacterial action. If you see overly sour, sluggish growth, or a thin, watery layer on top, it might suggest one population is becoming dominant or the starter is stressed. Regular visual inspection, coupled with monitoring the time it takes to double, offers a good proxy for the overall colony health.",
